06/03/2011
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- President Behgjet Pacolli's home in Pristina was searched on Saturday (March 5th) after police received an anonymous call claiming that a bomb had been planted there.
No device was found.
Pacolli was elected president on February 22nd by a narrow majority in parliament.
Opposition parties have challenged his election, citing alleged constitutional violations.
(Telegrafi, Alsat M, Koha Net - 05/03/11)
